Key Match Events: Trent Alexander-Arnold scored a stunning free-kick to make it 2-0 for England
Jack Grealish opened the scoring with a cool finish after a lovely flick from Angel Gomes
Pre-Game Insights: This was Lee Carsley's third game as interim manager for England
The team was expected to be more conventional due to the return of Harry Kane as the No. 9
Post-Match Reflections: Lee Carsley's interim tenure will likely end with his return to his old job with the under-21s
The team's performance was described as a return to the tranquil progress of Carsley's first camp
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was David Hytner's match report for The Guardian
The match was played at Helsinki Olympic Stadium
Others: England dominated the match against a limited Finland team
Declan Rice got the third goal for England from a cross by Ollie Watkins
